article.description:
Vickie Johnson scored 18 points and rookie Shanna
Zolman added 15 to help the San Antonio Silver Stars beat the
Houston Comets 79-63 on Sunday in the season opener for both teams.
article.headline: Silver Stars stop Comets in season opener for both teams
article.linkText: Silver Stars stop Comets in season opener for both
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Vickie Johnson scored 18 points in her first game
for San Antonio and rookie Shanna Zolman added 15 to help the
Silver Stars beat the Houston Comets 79-63 on Sunday in the season
opener for both teams.

With the victory, the Silver Stars ended a nine-game losing
streak dating to a 68-63 win in Houston on July 30.

"We just came out tonight and played aggressive," said
Johnson, the former New York Liberty player who had been playing in
Hungary until six days ago.

"I just got here and I can already tell that this team is just
going to get better. Tonight, we just did what we wanted to do and
that started with defense and great rebounding."

Sheryl Swoopes scored 19 points for the Comets, and Michelle
Snow added 13.

"It was just very ugly," Swoopes said. "It was very
frustrating to play the way we just did. Defensively, we are just
not getting it done and San Antonio is a team that we shouldn't
have given nearly 80 points to. San Antonio just gave it to us."

San Antonio led by as many as 17 points in the second half after
Johnson hit a 3-pointer with 3:53 left in the third quarter. The
Comets answered with a 7-2 run to cut it to 59-49, but Johnson hit
another 3-pointer to start the fourth quarter and the Silver Stars
cruised to their third season-opening win since moving to San
Antonio.
